{"questionId": "23a951fb-833f-4b27-9978-4eb054f855e2_7", "correctAnswer": "0.3,3/10", "section": "Math", "steps": [{"title": "Substitute the value x = 6", "content": "Replace $x$ with $6$ in $$f(x) = \\frac{x-3}{x^2-7x+16}.$$ This gives $$f(6) = \\frac{6-3}{(6)^2-7(6)+16}.$$"}, {"title": "Compute the result", "content": "Simplify: $$f(6) = \\frac{3}{36-42+16} = \\frac{3}{10}.$$ The answer is <strong>0.3,3/10</strong>."}]}